File: Huge disruptions are expected for taxi commuters as the National Taxi Association goes on strike. Silindelo Masikane/eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Some commuters could be left stranded on Wednesday morning as the National Taxi Alliance (NTA) embarks on strike action.
The NTA wants government to fast-track the payout of the COVID-19 relief fund. READ: New union for taxi drivers launched The industry was hit hard by the pandemic as taxis were not allowed to load at a hundred percent capacity during the hard lockdown. Long-distance taxis were also not operating as inter-provincial travelling was prohibited. READ: National taxi lekgotla resolves to regulate sector NTA members will march to the Union Buildings in Pretoria to hand over a memorandum to Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula.